sql:
SELECT item_name, price
FROM clothing_items
WHERE price = (SELECT MAX(price) FROM clothing_items);

SELECT item_name, price
FROM clothing_items
WHERE availability = 1;

SELECT AVG(price) AS average_price
FROM clothing_items
WHERE category = 'dresses';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT item_id) AS total_items_in_stock
FROM item_sizes
WHERE quantity > 0;

SELECT item_name, AVG(price) AS average_price
FROM clothing_items
GROUP BY item_name;

external_knowledge:
- 'shining stars' refers to the top-selling clothing items;
- 'sparkles of popularity' refers to total sales quantity;
- 'frequency of attraction' refers to the number of distinct orders.

- Captains of commerce: Customers who have placed orders;
- Shiploads of profit: Total sales from orders;
- Golden anchors: Average value of their orders;
- Depth of the treasure: Total sales value.

